history.content:
I'm not sure I'm understanding your question-if you want to change to a different lab, you would have to change to a different section.

As long as there is room in your new lab and your enrollment priority group, which I can't tell since you're anonymous, you will be enrolled off the waitlist once it's processed automatically. I'll be in the office until 12PM tomorrow if you run into trouble, but please make sure your new lab is open and you have a seat in your category, otherwise I can't help.

children.subject:
Did we meet in person yesterday?

In any case, the LSCS 5-6 terms in attendance category has filled. If you're enrolled in this category, you should still be able to switch to an open section, but you would be bumped to the waitlist at position #1 and then re-enrolled when the waitlist processes automatically at 8AM and 5PM. If you choose a full section, however, you would not be re-enrolled when the WL processes.

My erollment priority group is LS CS junior (in my 5th semester currently). What happens in that case?

Thanks!
